\f0\fs24 \cf0 # Smart Timer-Controlled Motor System with Keypad Input\
\
## Project Overview\
\
This project is a microcontroller-based smart timer system that allows users to control a motor for a custom duration using a 4x4 keypad interface. The system provides real-time feedback via an I2C LCD display and includes servo actuation and LED indicators for enhanced interaction.\
\
The motor acts as the main platform where **Peltier modules are directly fixed to the motor pins/assembly**, enabling controlled heating or cooling during operation. This makes the system suitable for temperature-based applications.\
\
---\
\
## Features\
\
* Custom time input using a 4x4 keypad\
* Real-time countdown display on 16x2 LCD\
* Motor control using H-bridge driver\
* Integration of **Peltier modules for heating/cooling**\
* Dual servo motor actuation\
* Visual feedback using LED indicators\
* Input validation and reset functionality\
* Simple and user-friendly interface\
\
---\
\
## Components Used\
\
* Arduino (Uno / Nano / compatible board)\
* 4x4 Matrix Keypad\
* 16x2 LCD with I2C module\
* Motor driver (L298N or similar)\
* DC fans\
* **Peltier Modules (Thermoelectric Coolers)**\
* 2 \'d7 Servo Motors\
* LEDs (2 \'d7 for status indication)\
* Resistors (for LEDs)\
* Power supply (5V / 12V depending on motor and Peltier requirements)\
\
